The paper deals with channel estimation in wireless communication, which is a common topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The use of compressed sensing to exploit the sparsity of the channel is also a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could fall under the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
